comments: Ayton (PHX) makes contact to the head/face of George (LAC) on the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Jackson (LAC) makes marginal contact to the body of Payne (PHX) during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) makes incidental contact to the arm of Kennard (LAC) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) hooks Beverley (LAC) on the drive and makes contact to his head/face area that affects his ability to defend.
Booker (PHX) engages in arm to arm contact and dislodges George (LAC) from his position while trying to defend him around the screen.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Kennard (LAC) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Booker (PHX) makes marginal contact to the body of George (LAC) during his drive that he is able to move through and continue his play towards the rim.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Replay review confirmed that the ball went out of bounds off of Booker (PHX) and LAC was rewarded with possession.
Bridges (PHX) commits a take foul on George (LAC).
Jackson (LAC) briefly grasps Bridges' (PHX) arm and the contact does not affect his FOM.
Jackson (LAC) legally contests Bridges' (PHX) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Booker (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Zubac (LAC) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Ayton (PHX) briefly grasps Zubac's (LAC) jersey and releases it as he goes around the screen.

Replay review confirms a successful basket by Ayton (PHX).  A player may touch a throw-in that enters the area above the basket cylinder.  For a violation to occur, a ball which is alive must enter the cylinder area after having been legally touched on the playing court. All players must consider this type of play as an ordinary throw-in and anyone may attempt to gain possession of the ball without penalty.
